27/05/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Deputy Prime Minister Plamen Panayotov said on Wednesday (26 May) that one of the country's major priorities at next month's NATO summit in Istanbul would be to preserve the "open door" policy for Macedonia, Croatia and Albania. The 28 June-29 June summit marks the first time Bulgaria will participate as a full NATO member.
In other news Wednesday, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy was in Ankara, where he thanked Turkey for supporting his country's NATO membership bid. He in turn pledged full Bulgarian support for Turkey's EU membership bid and said bilateral relations are at their highest point in 50 years. (BTA, BNT, Mediapool, Dnevnik, Anadolu Agency, NTV, bTV - 26/05/04)
